"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-uk-rhys-mcclenaghan-olympians-team-gb-paris-stormont-b1176898.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|UK  Two of Northern Ireland's Olympic gold medallists are set to be celebrated at a special homecoming event in Co Down later.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999988619847154, \"rank\": 1.1380120780440929e-06, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"GymnastRhys McClenaghanwon a gold medal in his specialist pommel horse event as part of Team Ireland at theParisGames, while swimmer Jack McMillan struck gold with theTeam GBmen's relay event.\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 450, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8668417330000795e-15, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.6791643631337162, \"rank\": 0.45335771478512876, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_McMillan\", \"score\": 0.999991746319621, \"rank\": 7.311195643426774e-06, \"text\": \"McMillan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_McMillan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nate_McMillan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be part of an event organised by Ards and North Down Council for the total 10 athletes from the borough who competed in this summer's Olympics for either Team Ireland or Team GB.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 608, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Down_Borough_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"North Down Council\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Down_Borough_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Down_Borough_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8668417330000795e-15, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999988194759, \"rank\": 1.1434251059804734e-09, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian competitor Abi Lyle and runner Rachel McCann will also be taking part in the public event at Conway Square in Newtownards this evening.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_McCann\", \"score\": 0.9999978234251143, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachel McCann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_McCann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_McCann\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newtownards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6125342257444476e-28, \"text\": \"Newtownards\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newtownards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newtownards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This has been Northern Ireland's most successful Olympic Games, with athletes from the region winning a record seven medals, including four gold in Paris.\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999988619847154, \"rank\": 1.1380120780440929e-06, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999962658421, \"rank\": 3.7340730109487585e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Homecoming events have already taken place for gold and bronze medallist swimmer Daniel Wiffen on Tuesday evening in Magheralin and for gold medallist rower Hannah Scott on Wednesday in Coleraine.\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 7.274618006069287e-13, \"text\": \"Magheralin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\"}, {\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coleraine\", \"score\": 0.9996575099308128, \"rank\": 0.0003426074069099739, \"text\": \"Coleraine\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coleraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coleraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"StormontCommunities Minister Gordon Lyons has said an official event will be held later this year to celebrate Northern Ireland's success at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Lyons\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gordon Lyons\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Lyons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gordon_Lyons\"}, {\"begin\": 1359, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999988619847154, \"rank\": 1.1380120780440929e-06, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is set to be open to the public, and also celebrate athletes who will take part in the Paralympic Games, which are due to start in Paris later this month.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999962658421, \"rank\": 3.7340730109487585e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want to celebrate ourOlympians, not just those that won medals, but also those that took part because it's an incredible achievement,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want to celebrate them and I also want to make sure that we have a lasting legacy.\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My officials have been tasked by me with creating a celebration appropriate to the fantastic achievements that we saw displayed in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999962658421, \"rank\": 3.7340730109487585e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1981, \"end\": 1990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999931613455926, \"rank\": 6.838022472247211e-06, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II